FBIS3-53160 "drnes008_j_94006" FBIS-NES-94-008 Document Type:Daily Report 12 Jan 1994 ARABIAN PENINSULA Yemen YSP Denies Undermining Unity JN1201064294 Paris Radio Monte Carlo in Arabic 0600 GMT 12 Jan 94 JN1201064294 Paris Radio Monte Carlo Language: Arabic Article Type:BFN [Text] According to Yemeni political sources, rival Yemeni parties have reached an agreement on political and military measures to put an end to the crisis which has paralyzed the Yemeni Government. It has been learned that a 27-member national dialogue committee has been set up to settle the differences between Yemeni President 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih and Vice President 'Ali Salim al-Bid, head of the Yemeni Socialist Party [YSP], with which Prime Minister Haydar Abu-Bakr al-'Attas is affiliated. The YSP denied charges it attributed to Yemeni President 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih that southern Yemeni leaders are seeking to undermine Yemeni unity through a conspiracy with Saudi Arabia and Kuwait. In a statement, the YSP affirmed that it will continue its firm course to improve Yemen's relations with its neighbors and halt all practices and reactions that harm Yemen's relations with its neighbors and prevent the promotion of these relations.
